Thailand Stocks: Bangchak, Khon Kaen, PTT, PTT Exploration

-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 
2011-09-23T06:15:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-23/thailand-stocks-bangchak-ptt-ptt-exploration-sri-trang-agro.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  Thailand  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 12:30 p.m. break in
Bangkok.  The SET Index slid 42.61 points, or 4.3 percent, to 947.98,
heading for the biggest drop since Oct. 15, 2009. The gauge has
declined 8.3 percent this week, set for the steepest loss since
October 2008.  Oil companies :  PTT Pcl (PTT)  , Thailand’s biggest energy
company, dropped 3.6 percent to 291 baht, poised for the lowest
close since Sept. 24, 2010.  PTT Exploration & Production Pcl (PTTEP) 
, the nation’s only publicly traded oil explorer, lost
2.5 percent to 154 baht.  Crude oil yesterday slid $5.41, or 6.3 percent, to $80.51 a
barrel on the  New York Mercantile Exchange , the lowest
settlement since Aug. 9.  Sugar producers:  Khon Kaen Sugar Industry Pcl (KSL)  
slumped 11 percent to 10.8 baht, poised for the largest drop
since October 2008. Khonburi Sugar Pcl (KBS TB) lost 9.5 percent
to 9.05 baht.  Raw-sugar futures for March delivery yesterday fell 4.2
percent to settle at 24.81 cents a pound on ICE Futures U.S. in
 New York , after touching 24.4 cents, the lowest since June 23.  Bangchak Petroleum Pcl (BCP)  , a state-controlled oil
refiner, fell 7.4 percent to 17.60 baht, bound for the largest
decrease since October 2008. The company changed its policy on
minimum dividend payments, reducing the level to 30 percent of
net income from 50 percent, it said in a regulatory filing. The
adjustment is to “provide sufficient cash” for future
investments amid an unstable economic environment, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anuchit Nguyen in Bangkok at 
